            },
            "answer_text": "The truth always works best. Illness is illness. Family emergency is family emergency. Your school system has a list of what constitutes an excused absence. Provided your legal guardian or parent signs the note, there shouldn\u2019t be an issue. Long term illness requiring an extended absence is generally best provided by a healthcare professional and notice is generally provided during the extended absence in an effort to keep up with assigned work. Chronic diarrhea may keep you out of school, but there is no reason it should prevent you from completing assignments. ",
